name: Terminal Spotting at San Francisco International Airport (Plane Spotting #12) ᴴᴰ
description:
Here we have my twelfth plane spotting compilation, this one from San Fransico International Airport, featuring lots of aircraft from United Airlines and a now retired Air New Zealand 747-400 (This was shot in February 2014). I have to apologize for the low quality of this upload, all of these clips were taken with my old camera, and as you all know, my freehand filming is, well, abysmal. There's some pretty cool stuff in here like a United 747 still in the tulip livery so I figured I might as well upload it. My upcoming videos will be of much better quality. 

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
____________________________________________________

Aircraft 1: United 757-200 N545UA Parked
Aircraft 2: United "Star Alliance" Livery 747-400 N121UA Taxiing
Aircraft 3: United Airlines 747-400 Taxiing
Aircraft 4: United Airlines 777-200 N779UA Parked
Aircraft 5: United 747-400 Under Tow 
Aircraft 6: United 777-200ER Takeoff 
Aircraft 7: United Airlines 747-400 Tulip Livery N174UA
Aircraft 8: United Airlines 757-300 Climb out
Aircraft 9: United Charter 747-400 Parked
Aircraft 10: United Airlines (surprise!) 757-300 Takeoff
Aircraft 11: Air New Zealand 747-400 ZK-SUH Rollout and Taxi
